Key Match Events: Cole Palmer scored England's first goal in the warm-up victory over Bosnia and Herzegovina
Trent Alexander-Arnold scored from a tight angle to put England 2-0 up
Harry Kane completed the scoring with a close-range finish
Pre-Game Insights: Gareth Southgate decided to introduce Harry Kane and other players from the bench
Cole Palmer was given the responsibility to take a penalty, which he successfully converted
James Maddison and Jack Grealish were also introduced as substitutes
Post-Match Reflections: Southgate praised the team's performance, especially the attacking riches
There was some concern about the defensive lineup due to injuries to key players
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ezri Konsa had a breakaway chance but his shot was saved by the goalkeeper
Nikola Katic grappled with Ollie Watkins, who might have gone to ground
Kieran Trippier and Jordan Pickford received mixed reactions from the crowd
